Date: Fri, 2 Dec 2022 02:35:56 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] ti_config_fragments: v8_audio_display: Reduce CMA size
 support Multimedia

When applying dtbos that reserve additional memory for the
remote cores, there is not enough space left for 512MB of
CMA allocation.

Reducing it to 360MB for codec to work with rtos-memory-map

Upstreaming status:
Upstreaming to CoreSDK targetted for 8.6: https://jira.itg.ti.com/browse/LCPD-29811

Signed-off-by: Aniket Limaye <a-limaye@ti.com>
---
 ti_config_fragments/v8_audio_display.cfg | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ti_config_fragments/v8_audio_display.cfg b/ti_config_fragments/v8_audio_display.cfg
index 1c3efa4d30..3e8a0a92c3 100644
--- a/ti_config_fragments/v8_audio_display.cfg
+++ b/ti_config_fragments/v8_audio_display.cfg
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@
 
 CONFIG_CMA=y
 CONFIG_DMA_CMA=y
-CONFIG_CMA_SIZE_MBYTES=512
+CONFIG_CMA_SIZE_MBYTES=360
 
 # backlight
 
